<h2><div style="text-align:center;">EXAMPLE FEED POSTS</div></h2>
<br/>
<span style="font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline;">Good Contribution:</span>
<br/><br/>
<ul style="font-weight: bold; margin:0; padding:0;">
  <li>“What have you done this week to improve customer satisfaction? Any good tips or tricks that customer seem to respond positively to?”
    <ul style="font-weight:normal;">
      <li>Motivating/challenging team communication.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>“Are paint codes found in the Product Guides ok to share with customers of is that restricted information?”
    <ul style="font-weight:normal;">
      <li>Reaching out for expertise and information.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>“Has everyone seen the new Knowledge eLearning module on Virtual Academy? It has some best practices in there for searching quickly that really helped me. ”
    <ul style="font-weight:normal;">
      <li>Providing useful information for other customer-facing agents.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<br/>
<span style="font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline;">Off Topic Contribution:</span>
<br/><br/>
<ul style="font-weight: bold; margin:0; padding:0;">
  <li>“Keep Jane in your prayers – she was recently diagnosed with breast cancer.”  
    <ul style="font-weight:normal;">
      <li>Lovely sentiment but sharing confidential medical information may violate the law.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>“Dealer ABC is going out of business and customer ABC wants to know if her service contract will change as a result.”
    <ul style="font-weight:normal;">
      <li>Valid question but is not appropriate for Chatter – keep it generic without mentioning specific dealer or customer names.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>“There’s an article published in the XYZ publication with a quote from an executive.  I can’t believe that’s really Nissan’s position on the topic.”
    <ul style="font-weight:normal;">
      <li>Reporting on business information but expresses opinion that is negative and embarrassing.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<br/><br/>
<h2><div style="text-align:center;">EXAMPLE FILE/DOCUMENT POSTS</div></h2>
<br/>
<span style="font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline;">Good File Contribution on Chatter:</span>
<ul style="margin:0; padding:0;">
  <li>News article link</li>
  <li>Industry or trend report </li>
  <li>Internal process or template</li>
  <li>Status report requiring comments/input</li>
  <li>Sales collateral or case study</li>
  <li>Competitive intelligence</li>
</ul>
